Learn how to write your first Verilog program.

---

# What is Hello World in Verilog?

Unlike C or Python, Verilog is a Hardware Description Language (HDL).  
To print text in the simulator console, we use the `$display` system task inside an `initial` block.

---

# Verilog Code

```verilog
module hello_world;

initial begin
    $display("Hello World!");
end

endmodule
```

---

# Code Explanation

### module hello_world;

Defines a hardware module named **hello_world**.

### initial

The statements inside the `initial` block execute only **once** at the start of simulation.

### $display

Prints text to the simulator console.

### endmodule

Marks the end of the module.

